                does your map represent the song?
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="font-bold">Map consistency</span>: Is the mapping
                consistent and does the difficulty of the map scale properly
                with the different parts of the song?
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="font-bold">Pattern creativity</span>: Are creative
                patterns (slider, circle patterns) used? Do they make sense with
                the song?
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="font-bold">General quality</span>: Is everything
                snapped and timed correctly? Is there a fitting background,
                combo colours? Is it hitsounded properly? Is the flow
                appropriate? Do the difficulty sliders make sense? Bonus points
                may be awarded for storyboards.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="font-bold">Era representation</span>: How well are
                old mapping techniques applied?
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="font-bold">Modernization</span>: How well would the
                map be received by a modern audience? How does you map contrast
